snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS Sporting CP 4-1 Man City | Foden, Gyorkeres hat-trick & Araujo goals
snippet.description:
City suffered a night of Champions League disappointment, losing out 4-1 at Sporting CP with Viktor Gyokeres hitting a hat-trick for the hosts.

Pep Guardiola‚Äôs side had got off to a flying start in Lisbon going ahead thanks to a fourth minute goal from Phil Foden.

The Blues ‚Äì who handed teenage defender Jahmai Simpson-Pusey a full debut ‚Äì dominated the first half carving out a host of other chances.

But, out of nowhere, Gyokeres struck to level affairs late in the first half before Sporting then scored twice within three minutes at the start of the second half through Maximiliano Araujo and Gyokeres, via a penalty, to seize control.

snippet.description:
How Gautam Adani became India's second-richest person being first-generation entrepreneur. He didn't build businesses; he acquired them and revamped them. 

Adani recognised the value of established assets. He focused on infrastructure and essential industries. Where others saw obstacles, Adani saw opportunity. With moves that transformed ports, power, and logistics, he laid the groundwork for an empire that spans industries‚Äîfrom seaports to airports, mining to manufacturing.

Today, he‚Äôs not just a business magnate; he‚Äôs the King of Infrastructure, a visionary who plays on a scale that has made his name synonymous with ambition and growth.

How Adani built stable revenue streams and gave his business a new footing through long-term contracts, networking, and opportunity scanning? In this 12th episode of ‚ÄúTycoons of India‚Äù, Dr Vivek Bindra explains in detail the 9 business strategies that played a key role in Adani's success-

Strategy 1: Network is your Net worth
Strategy 2: Amplification of Network
Strategy 3: Opportunity Scanner
Strategy 4: Skin in the Game
Strategy 5: Boring Bijli Business
Strategy 6: CNG-PNG-LNG- Integrated Strength
Strategy 7: Local Edge Partnership
Strategy 8: Sector Assimilation Strategy
Strategy 9: Value Based Bidding
